<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <%- include('includes/head', { title: 'How to file a claim', nonce: nonce }) %>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.folder/possibleDisabilities.css" />

  <body>
    <div class="page-wrapper">
      <%- include('includes/header', { nonce: nonce }) %>

      <div class="container">
      <h1>How to file a claim</>
      <h2>Step 0</h2>
         <p>VA disability is following 3 major requirements </p>
           <p>Connection to your service. The onset of your condition needs to be linked to the time of active service</p>
           <p>The condition needs to be chronic</p>
           <p>It has to affect your ability to perform your daily duties and responsibilities</p>
      <h3>Dirrect connection claim</h3>
      <h2>Step 1</h2>
         <p>Start the intent to file</p>
         <p>Once you start the claim application, it starts the intent to file countdown, and you will have 1 year to submit your claims. This will accumulate the retroactive payout in case you need some additional time to prepare your claim</p>
      <h2>Step 2</h2>
         <p>FOIA (Freedom of Information Act)</p>
           <p>Request a full military record through <a href="https://www.va.gov/find-forms/about-form-20-10206/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> FOIA (VA Form 20-10206)</a></p>
           <p>The request execution might take up to 1 year</p>
           <p>A Full military record is needed to have access to documents, evidence, important dates, appointments, treatments, and testing records</p>
         <h2>Step 3</h2>
           <p>Write a good personal statement that shows the medical condition connection to your time in service, the onset event, or a reason why you think your disability is connected to your service</p>
           <p>Include a detailed description of how this disability affects your personal, social life, and employment. </p>
           <p>If possible, request witness statements about your condition and how it affects you from close family, friends, or co-workers. Someone who has first-hand knowledge of your condition (Lay Statements)</p>
           <p>If possible, request witness statements about your condition and how it affects you from someone who served with you. 
              Buddy statements are especially valuable to prove things that might not be in your service records — like stressors, injuries, or events in the field (Buddy Statements)</p>
           <p> Gather all the medical records of any specific condition-related visit to a medical professional outside the VA </p>
           <p>If VA medical records are available through Blue Button, FOIA, or Inservice records, highlight the events that pertain to the specific disability claim and create a separate file consisting of pages with highlighted references.</p>
           
        <div class="spacer"></div>
      </div> <!-- closes .container -->

      <%- include('includes/footer') %>
    </div> <!-- closes .page-wrapper -->

    <!-- Your existing scripts -->
    <script src="/js/mobile-drawer.js" nonce="<%= nonce %>"></script>
    <script src="/js/symptomAnalysis.js" nonce="<%= nonce %>" defer></script>
  </body>
</html>
